org.ftccommunity.org.ftccommunity.ftcxtensible.robot

Class ExtensibleLoopManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ftccommunity.org.ftccommunity.ftcxtensible.robot.ExtensibleLoopManager

  • @NotDocumentedWell
public class ExtensibleLoopManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the configuration manager for how ExtensibleOpMode loops. You can use to change how the loops behave, whether to skip loops, set a different recurring loop as a replacement, and so forth
    Since:
    0.2.0
    Author:
    David Sargent

    • Method Detail

      • registerNewLoopOnEveryX

        protected ExtensibleLoopManager registerNewLoopOnEveryX(int loopX,
                                                        OpModeLoop loop)
        Requests to have a different loop run if the loop number is a multiple of the loopX parameter. This replaces the previous loop, if there was a previous loop associated with the val for loopX. The replacement only runs when ExtensibleOpMode.getLoopCount() % loopX == 0 is true
        Parameters:
        loopX - how many loops should occur prior to this loop
        loop - the replacement loop
        Returns:
        the current ExtensibleLoopManager

      • unregisterNewLoopOnEveryX

        protected ExtensibleLoopManager unregisterNewLoopOnEveryX(int loopX)
                                                   throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Removes the alternative loop to use when ExtensibleOpMode.getLoopCount() % loopX == 0 is true
        Parameters:
        loopX - how many loops should be in between the execution of the alternative loops
        Returns:
        the current instance of ExtensibleLoopManager
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if there if no registered replacement for the loop
